HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 304
BY REPRESENTATIVE DESHOTEL
A RESOLUTION
To commend the Louisiana Oil Marketers Association on the occasion of its seventy-fifth
anniversary and to designate Wednesday, May 20, 2026, as Louisiana Oil Marketers
Association Day in Louisiana.
WHEREAS, the Louisiana Oil Marketers Association (LOMA) represents more than
two hundred fifty member companies that own, operate, or supply over three thousand
convenience stores, service stations, car washes, truck stops, and related motor fuel retail
outlets throughout Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, LOMA members annually supply nearly three billion gallons of motor
fuel to serve Louisiana motorists and a wide range of commercial users, including farmers,
construction firms, and state and local governmental entities; and
WHEREAS, petroleum marketers play an essential role in the energy and
transportation infrastructure of Louisiana by ensuring the reliable distribution and resale of
refined petroleum products across wholesale and retail markets; and
WHEREAS, LOMA was founded seventy-five years ago by a group of jobbers
meeting at the Jung Hotel in Shreveport, Louisiana, who sought to establish an organization
to support and advance the petroleum marketing industry through shared services, advocacy,
and professional collaboration; and
WHEREAS, over the decades, LOMA has evolved into a statewide trade association
headquartered in Baton Rouge that provides political representation, educational
programming, industry publications, scholarships, and annual conventions and trade shows
that strengthen Louisiana's convenience store and petroleum marketing industries; and
