WHEREAS, LOMA continues to address the evolving needs of its members,
including fair competition, regulatory compliance, underground storage tank issues, fuel
theft prevention, and other matters critical to the industry; and
WHEREAS, LOMA members contribute significantly to the economy of Louisiana
by investing in local communities, creating jobs, and providing essential goods and services
in both urban and rural areas of the state; and
WHEREAS, the seventy-fifth anniversary of LOMA represents a milestone of
enduring service and economic contribution, and the Louisiana Oil Marketers Association
is deserving of recognition for its legacy of service to the citizens of the state.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend the Louisiana Oil Marketers Association on
the occasion of its seventy-fifth anniversary and does hereby designate Wednesday, May 20,
2026, as Louisiana Oil Marketers Association Day in Louisiana.
